<div class="row">
    <div class="span4">
        <h2>UTF8Grid</h2>
        <p>Mapstache aids in the creation of  <a href="http://mapbox.com/developers/utfgrid/">UTF8Grid</a> tiles.</p>
        <p>Generate UTF8Grid tiles to make your maps more interactive. UTFGrids can be used to output highly optimized feature "hit grids."
            The UTFGrid encoding scheme encodes interactivity data for a tile in a
            space efficient manner. It is designed to be used in browsers for
            interactive features like displaying tooltips without having to hit the
            server for an "info query". </p>
        
        @* <p><a class="btn" href="#">View details &raquo;</a></p>*@
    </div>
    <div class="span4">
        <h2>WMTS</h2>
        <p>Generate <a href="http://www.opengeospatial.org/standards/wmts">WMTS</a> tiles to be displayed in OpenLayers using SQL Server to store your geospatial inforation. </p>
        <p>WMTS is a good approach if you can cache the generated tiles on the server.</p>
        @*<p><a class="btn" href="#">View details &raquo;</a></p>*@
    </div>
    <div class="span4">
        <h2>WMS</h2>
        <p>Generate WMS layers to be displayed in OpenLayers using data stored in SQL Server.</p>
        <p>WMS is a good approach if the data does not lend itself to caching e.g.. live tracking of GPS data.</p>
    @*  <p><a class="btn" href="#">View details &raquo;</a></p>*@
    </div>
</div>
